<br>
As to bash:  enchanters do not have bash coded in, because enchanters cannot be a race that slams.  Rogues, however, can be barbarians, thus a rogue with the barbarian illusion mask can slam (with one point of skill in it, and it is on the backstab timer, ugh).  Note that the reverse is also true... a large race character cannot slam if illusioned into something smaller.<br>
<br>
Other bonuses to illusions exist (water elemental gives enduring breath, earth elemental gives some strength I think, air elemental gives levitate).  But these are special to those spells.  As a rule, pure illusion spells give the vision, size, and look of the character, and nothing else.  But since slam is size based, it is affected.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taerinblackmaul>Taerin Blackmaul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kaladim Cutie</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/5/03 2:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes, troll gives about 3/tick</span><hr size=1> *peeks into the Fighter's Den, not for sure why she's really in here and then listens in on the barsh question*<br>
